 You climb the proverbial ladder and as you stand at that spot,

498
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:54,000
 you realize there's only one more rung to climb.

499
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:59,000
 You're still in fact as far behind as another group of people as you felt

500
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:02,000
 from where you first were before.

501
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:07,000
 You're not nearly as happy here as you anticipated you would.

502
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:09,000
 This is with your career.

503
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,000
 This could be in anything.

504
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,000
 This could be in relationships.

505
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,000
 This could be in reputation.

506
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,000
 I want to be someone that's admirable, respected.

507
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:18,000
 I want to make a difference in the world.

508
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:21,000
 It could be something about pleasure, experience.

509
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:24,000
 Listen, these things are not inherently bad.

510
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:26,000
 In fact, they're pretty important.

511
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:31,000
 Career, relationship, reputation, these things are good things.

512
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,000
 They're important things.

513
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:37,000
 Porch, they're not ultimate things.

514
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:43,000
 And thus, because they are not ultimate, they will never satisfy.

515
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:50,000
 They will not deliver on the promise they've made that fullness is right here.

516
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:53,000
 Step right up and take as much as you want.

517
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:56,000
 How do I know that that's the case?

518
00:27:56,000 --> 00:28:03,000
 Because there is one who is ultimate where fullness is actually found.

519
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,000
 That's what Paul says.

520
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:11,000
 He says in verse 9, "For in him, the whole fullness of deity dwells bodily,

521
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:17,000
 and you have been filled in him who is the head of all rule and authority."

522
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:20,000
 All the fullness of God dwells in this man, Jesus.

523
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:25,000
 So all the fullness you seek, guess where it's found?

524
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:27,000
 In him as well.

525
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,000
 It's interesting.

526
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:32,000
 I talk to young adults all the time.

527
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:36,000
 And as I visit with them, often what I find myself engaging in conversation about

528
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:41,000
 is that their job just isn't as life-giving as they thought it would be.

529
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:44,000
 Or their friend group's just not as life-giving as they thought it would be.

530
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:47,000
 Or that commitment they made, that leadership position they have,

531
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:49,000
 that volunteer role they hold.

532
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:51,000
 Man, it's just not giving me life.

533
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:57,000
 It's not supposed to.

534
00:28:57,000 --> 00:29:02,000
 No job, no relationship, no group of friends is supposed to give you life.

535
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 For us to say that language in the church, within the walls of this own building,

536
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:12,000
 shows that the world has permeated our midst.

537
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,000
 It's come inside.

538
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:19,000
 I'm looking at you and it's saying, "There is something we could add to Jesus."

539
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,000
 Have you thought about X, Y, and Z?

540
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:25,000
 Those things are not meant to give you life.

541
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,000
 He is.

542
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:29,000
 That's why all things are meant to be done to the glory of God,

543
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 because it's in the glory of God that you find rich satisfaction.

544
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 This statement, "fullness of deity" that Paul uses,

545
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 it's loaded with meaning.

546
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 Because in the Old Testament, any time the word "fullness" pops up,

547
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:49,000
 it's most often talking about the presence of God, the fullness of God.

548
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:54,000
 And any time "deity" pops up, it's talking about the essence of God.

549
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,000
 So when he says "fullness of deity,"

550
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:04,000
 he's saying the presence and the expression, the essence of God,

551
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:07,000
 they're found in Jesus.

552
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 All of God's person, his being, and all of his personality, his doing,

553
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,000
 it's in him.

554
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,000
 That's where you can find it.

555
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:19,000
 That's why fullness is available.

556
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:23,000
 What Paul is getting at is that Jesus is God.

557
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 Unbelievable.

558
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,000
 Have you seen him?

559
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:29,000
 He's unbelievable.

560
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:33,000
 Become God perceivable.

561
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:36,000
 He is God's transcendence.

562
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 He is God's eminence.

563
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 Power in the form of a person.

564
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,000
 That's what we talked about last week.

565
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:46,000
 And that's what Paul is hammering at right here.

566
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:48,000
 He's the fullness of God.

567
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,000
 So in him we find the fulfillment for ourselves.

568
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 But it's not just that.

569
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 In verse 11, "In him also you were circumcised with a circumcision made without hands,

570
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 by putting off the body of the flesh, by the circumcision of Christ,

571
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,000
 having been buried with him in baptism,

572
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:04,000
 in which you were also raised with him through faith in the powerful working of God,

573
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:07,000
 who raised him from the dead."

574
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 Without getting into too much detail,

575
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:12,000
 circumcision was a physical sign in the Old Testament for the people of God

576
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
 that Paul is referencing right here to refute this claim

577
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 that because the Colossians are not ethnic Jews,

578
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 they can't be a part of the people of God.

579
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:22,000
 You're not circumcised, so you can't be in here.

580
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 He's saying that's not true.

581
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:26,000
 That's not actually the case.

582
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 He's saying, no, it's not by human hands that you become a part of God's family.

583
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 It's by way of God's own hands.

584
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:34,000
 That's what he does.

585
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,000
 It's not a circumcision physically.

586
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 It's a circumcision spiritually.

587
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 It's of the heart.

588
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:46,000
 He says it like this in Romans 2, 29.

589
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 "But a Jew, an ethnic Jew, is one inwardly,

590
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 and circumcision is a matter of the heart."

591
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:02,000
 He's saying if you want to be identified with the people of God,

592
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 it's not by blood, it's by spirit.

593
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,000
 That happens inwardly.

594
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:10,000
 Circumcision is a matter of the heart by God's spirit,

595
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 not by the letter of the law.

596
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:15,000
 His praise is not from man, it's from God.

597
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,000
 Which is good news to us.

598
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 Because what Paul is saying is,

599
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 if you want to be in the family of God,

600
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:27,000
 the door is open for anyone and everyone.

601
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:30,000
 There is no barrier to entry.

602
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 You can come in here.

603
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,000
 You can grab a seat at the table.

604
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:37,000
 Anyone is welcome here because God is the one that brings people into his family,

605
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,000
 and he does not discriminate.

606
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,000
 Everyone is welcome right here.

607
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:43,000
 How, Paul?

608
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:44,000
 How is that the case?

609
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:48,000
 Because that unbelievable God that has become a perceivable God in Jesus,

610
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:50,000
 don't miss this,

611
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:54,000
 has also become a receivable God.

612
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:56,000
 He's not just a God you can know.

613
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 He's a God you can have.

614
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,000
 Because that's Jesus' heart.

615
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,000
 He wants you in his family.

616
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:04,000
 That's why he came.

617
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:06,000
 He came to cross the divide,

618
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:11,000
 to bridge the void and bring you back to God himself.

619
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 And not just save you from your sin,

620
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 but save you into a whole new way of life

621
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 in fullness forevermore.

622
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 The reason this matters for our room

623
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 is because some of us here

624
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 feel a lot like these Colossians.

625
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 We do feel like there's a barrier to entry for us.

626
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:36,000
 We do feel like we don't belong in the family of God.

627
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,000
 We look at ourselves and we say,

628
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 "You don't know what I've done."

629
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 "Have you seen my resume,

630
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 the mistakes that are littered thereupon?"

631
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 "I'm disqualified from this thing."

632
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 "I'm unqualified to get in."

633
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 "I'm inadequate to be a part of God's family."

634
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:57,000
 "I have a stain so deep, no one can clean it."

635
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:59,000
 And yet God is looking at you and saying,

636
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:01,000
 "No, I can clean it."

637
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,000
 "How?"

638
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:04,000
 "By my own blood."

639
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,000
 "I will clean you."

640
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:08,000
 "I will wash you out of snow."

641
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:10,000
 "I will bring you to myself."

642
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 "And you will remain with me forever."

643
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
 This is such good news

644
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 because it's not a result of anything we do.

645
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,000
 It is in spite of everything we've done

646
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:24,000
 that we come into the family of God.

647
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:26,000
 And it's through the person of Jesus.

648
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:28,000
 That's what Paul unpacks for us

649
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:30,000
 as we continue into our final point.

650
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,000
 He says in verse 13,

651
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:34,000
 "And you, who were dead in your trespasses

652
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:36,000
 and the uncircumcision of your flesh,

653
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 God made alive together with him,

654
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:40,000
 having forgiven us all our trespasses,

655
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 by canceling the record of debt that stood against us

656
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 with its legal demands.

657
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:47,000
 This he set aside, nailing it to the cross.

658
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:49,000
 He disarmed the rulers and authorities,

659
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 and he put them to open shame

660
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:56,000
 by triumphing over them in him."

661
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 Paul turns the corner,

662
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,000
 and he gives us our final lesson

663
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:04,000
 that those fully forgiven should live fully free.

664
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:07,000
 Those fully forgiven should live fully free.

665
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:10,000
 What's the best motivation for living free?

666
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:13,000
 The reminder of what you've been freed from, right?

667
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 Anytime I speak to my nieces and my nephews

668
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,000
 and I learn about their schoolwork,

669
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 I rejoice, man, 'cause those days are behind me, you know?

670
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,000
 I'm reminded of what I've been freed from.

671
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,000
 I have graduated from the imprisonment

672
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:27,000
 of my former education,

673
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:32,000
 and now I don't have to do those things any longer.

674
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:35,000
 When you're reminded of what you've been freed from,

675
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:39,000
 you're motivated to live into your freedom.

676
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:41,000
 That's what Paul's pointing to.

677
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,000
 That's why he spends the next three verses

678
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 unpacking specifically three problems

679
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,000
 we've been delivered from.

680
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:49,000
 He wants to add fuel to your freedom.

681
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:52,000
 He wants to pour gas onto your gratitude.

682
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:56,000
 So what are the three things that we've been delivered from?

683
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:59,000
 Verse 13, regret from our past.

684
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
 Verse 14, debt for our sin.

685
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 And verse 15, threat of the enemy.

686
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:09,000
 Regret from our past.

687
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,000
 These are the things which result

688
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 from the trespasses Paul talks about in verse 13,

689
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:18,000
 which raises the question, what does it mean to trespass?

690
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:21,000
 In the Greek, it literally means to take a false step,

691
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 to go somewhere you're not supposed to be.

692
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,000
 When I was in high school,

693
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:29,000
 every summer my youth group, we would take a mission trip,

694
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:31,000
 which meant every summer,

695
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 we would inevitably prank the girls.

696
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,000
 The boys would go on this trip,

697
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:39,000
 and we would, like a thief in the night,

698
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,000
 try to prank the girls.

699
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:43,000
 We would try to go into their quarters

700
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:46,000
 and absolutely wreak havoc and leave them a memory

701
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:49,000
 worth telling about for days forward.

702
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,000
 How would we do it?

703
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 We would trespass.

704
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:54,000
 That's how we would do it.

705
00:36:54,000 --> 00:37:00,000
 We would sneak into their room under the cover of nightfall.

706
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:04,000
 We would do so after our chaperones had fallen asleep.

707
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 We would execute plans that we had carefully

708
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 and meticulously prepared.

709
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:14,000
 Plans that included things like cling-wrapping toilets

710
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:17,000
 and hanging cheese puffs above their door

711
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:19,000
 so that when they opened it, it would rain down upon them,

712
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,000
 filling their shower heads with Kool-Aid

713
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:23,000
 so that we would leave them oh-so-sticky.

714
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:25,000
 Very devious exploits.

715
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,000
 This is what we would do.

716
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:31,000
 We would trespass in order to make it happen.

717
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:35,000
 We would go someplace we shouldn't have been

718
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:39,000
 to do something we shouldn't have done.

719
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,000
 This is what Paul's talking about.

720
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:46,000
 He's saying, "Hey, you've not only trespassed

721
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:51,000
 "against one another, you have trespassed against God."

722
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:53,000
 We've lived our lives selfishly,

723
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:56,000
 hating God, hurting one another.

724
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,000
 Romans says that even our conscience

725
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:00,000
 bears witness against us, that intrinsically,

726
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:05,000
 we know the world is not as it should be, nor am I.

727
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:08,000
 And so he's saying, "Hey, you are filled with regret.

728
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:13,000
 "You know you are not doing what you should,

729
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:19,000
 "and you have good reason for doing it right."

730
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:24,000
 And yet, because of what Jesus Christ has done upon his cross,

731
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:28,000
 he has answered for every single one of our trespasses.

732
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:30,000
 Everything we've done wrong,

733
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,000
 every place we never should have been,

734
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,000
 he has borne the full consequence of it

735
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,000
 in himself upon his cross.

736
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:39,000
 And thus, we have no reason to regret any longer.

737
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:41,000
 We have every reason to rejoice.

738
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:43,000
 That's what he's pointing towards.

739
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:46,000
 We have been freed from our regret.

740
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:49,000
 We have absolutely been relinquished from those things

741
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:52,000
 which held us in shame and guilt and condemnation.

742
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,000
 But it's not just that.

743
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:55,000
 We've not just been freed from our regret.

744
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:58,000
 We've also been freed from debt of our sin.

745
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:00,000
 Verse 14 says that God made us alive

746
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:02,000
 by canceling the record of debt that stood against us

747
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:04,000
 with its legal demands.

748
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,000
 This he set aside.

749
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:06,000
 He nailed it to the cross.

750
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,000
 What does that mean?

751
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:13,000
 Our sin against God had racked up a huge tab,

752
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:17,000
 one that we could not pay.

753
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:24,000
 And so Jesus stepped in our place,

754
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:27,000
